# Plan: Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js already defines `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/models.js` (line 8736), backed by 11 multimodal architectures (Florence-2, LLaVA, SmolVLM, Qwen2-VL, etc.). However, no pipeline class exists to expose this model family to end users. This plan wires up the missing pipeline so users can call `pipeline('image-text-to-text', model)` and pass an image + text prompt to get a generated text response.

**Primary reference files:**
- `ImageToTextPipeline` — same output shape, same use of processor + tokenizer + `model.generate()`
- `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` — same two-arg `_call(image, text)` signature pattern
- `SUPPORTED_TASKS["image-to-text"]` — nearest multimodal entry in the task registry

---

## Critical Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/pipelines.js` | All changes happen here |
| `src/models.js` | Read-only reference — `AutoModelForImageTextToText` at line 8736 |

---

